    <p>This document describes the process for installing HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade.</p>
    <section id="about-the-installation">
      <title>About the installation</title>
      <p>The HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade installation installs a virtual machine for the
        lifecycle manager VM, creates a base HP Helion OpenStack cloud, and deploys a carrier grade
        cloud.
        <!--You can also optionally install a baremetal region that leverages the OpenStack Ironic service.-->
        HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade uses <xref
          href="../Overview/carrier-grade-overview.dita#topic4010/networking">Accelerated vSwitch
          (AVS)</xref> networking. </p>
      <p>After installation, you can interact with the HP Helion OpenStack cloud using the <xref
          href="../ServicesOverviews/carrier-grade-services-horizon-overview.dita">Horizon graphical
          interface</xref> or using the CLIs of the respective <xref
          href="../../CarrierGrade2.1/Overview/carrier-grade.services-overview.dita"
          >services</xref> to manage hypervisors and provision virtual machines.</p>
    </section>
